  "body": "Successfully synced with launch. Turned it off, and when I turned it back on this morning, it doesn't sync, or syncs in fits & starts (very unreliably at least). Looking at the debug, I keep seeing this.\n\n\"dyn dial conn 33538128d0e816bf 77.53.40.242:30303 failed proto handshake: Too many peers\"\n\nI receive this even when I have zero peers connected. It never goes higher than 4 - 6 even if I set maxpeers to say 50.\n\nIs this error because \"other\" peers aren't allowing me to connect? Or is my own node that's spitting that out? Are other peers kicking me off?\n\nWhat's happening here?\n",
