    "body": "I'd think it's not really a fault at your end, or at any other place either imho. We should add a node removal strategy to ensure new joiners can quickly get a slot into the network. We just need to figure out a way that doesn't introduce DOS vulnerabilities with malicious nodes piling up on an unsuspecting node. It will be addressed eventually, but may take a bit depending on the seriousness of the issue. Maybe @fjl can make a mental note that this might become an issue eventually so we could start thinking about this scenario.\n",
